section.code:
Inputs: - exam_date: "2026-07-15" - candidate_state: {"people": 0.6, "process": 0.5, "business_environment": 0.2} # 0.0 = none, 1.0 = mastered - weekly_hours: 8 - weights: {"people": 0.33, "process": 0.41, "business_environment": 0.26}
Output JSON: { "weeks_until_exam": <int>, "weekly_plan": [{"week": 1, "focus": "...", "hours": {...}}], "gap_topics": ["sustainability", "governance", ...], "recommended_resources": [{"title":"...","url":"...","domain":"..."}] }
Rules: - Allocate hours proportional to (weight - mastery), not weight alone. - Cite ECO task IDs when listing topics. - Refuse to invent question banks; require user-provided source.
